column5: Congratulations Terry!!!  Enjoy every minute!!
I’ve been retired since 39. I’m bored and feel like looking for a job again....
theres just sooooo many lakes to fish...and it sounds like you dont have a solid enough of a fishing partner lol
As much as yer daily texts of fishing during the weekdays piss me off, I know you have earned yer days. I will get there. Later then sooner,BUT, I,ll will get there. LOL
Congrats Terry! enjoy it!
Piss off already. LOL
right on - enjoy! I can see you slowly paddling out, all relaxed in the pontoon as Brian heads in to work on his ,
Wow!!! seriously Terry?  Congrats!!! Must be EARLY retirement?
Enjoy it Terry. I took freedom 54 at the end of june.
Congratulation Terry, retirement is a wonderful occupation. ?
Good to hear you have reached the best times of your life. Art
Congrats Terry.   The fish will be scared.
Congratulations, time will fly by, be warned,  I can't believe its been ten years last month since I punched my last card.
Heck, he even fished on a Saturday, or is everyday Saturday now ?
What day is it anyways
Congrats Terry! Lake Simcoe is going to be taking a beating! It also means that you have more time to fix stuff! LOL Congrats! HH
Oh man am so jealous! Being self employed I'm working on the freedom 95 plan? LOL Congrats!!!! ENJOY!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Dan.
"Work is over rated" ""I work 1 day in last 10 years and regret it"" Have fun pissing people off.
i hate you right now........

Congats Terry. Instead of retiring I have limited my days and hours to my preference. My work needs a withdrawal pace lol. If I take 3 days vacation  I’m guaranteed 10 day at least! have great one on the lake.
any tips on how i can retire tomorrow as well? im 30 lol
Sure do what I did   punch your boss in the face quick and complete retirement lol
